MAGAZINE QUANTITIES ARE VERY LIMITED!!

The next generation of AR magazines has arrived and INTRAFUSE is at the forefront with Tapco's 30rd Gen II AR Magazine. It still retains the rugged mag body that the original had, but Tapco has made vast changes to the interior components to improve the overall functionality of the magazine. title: For Sale:  Springfield Armory Trophy Match 1911 .45ACP
postcontent:
This gun Springfield Armory Trophy Match 1911 is previously owned by one owner.

The Trophy Match 1911 is the flagship 1911 pistol in the Springfield Armory line. It comes with every feature you could possibly need, and is made to the most exacting specifications.

The frame and slide are made from forged steel. The rounded surfaces of the frame and slide are bead-blasted, while the flats are polished; giving the pistol a distinctive and classy look. The hardwood Cocobolo grips stand out nicely against the blued steel frame.
The match grade barrel is made from stainless steel, and is supported at the front with a stainless match grade barrel bushing. The guide rod is two-piece, which is the original 1911 style.

The sights are fully adjustable target style. The front sight is dovetail mounted into the slide. The adjustable sights are made by Novak, and are considered to be some of the best on the market. The rear notch and front sight blade align with just enough "air" around the sight picture to let you know that your sight blade is centered. Once adjusted, they stay adjusted, even after thousands of rounds.

The trigger is match grade as well, and is slightly longer than on other models, putting the first pad of most shooters' trigger fingers right on the front face. The pull on the trigger is 4.5 to 5 pounds, perfect for target shooting. The trigger is adjustable for over travel, too.

The slide has angled serrations on the front and rears, letting you grasp the slide with either hand quickly. The front strap is checkered for a solid grip.

An ambidextrous safety makes the pistol more easily used by left-handed shooters, or those who shoot with either hand.

The magazine well is wide at the bottom, and is bevelled to allow you to insert the magazine quickly without looking. The two supplied magazines have slam pads to aid in fast insertion. 

What more could you ask for?

The price includes shipping/handling. Missouri residents must pay state sales taxes. 

Firearms may only be shipped to a licensed dealer (FFL Holder). It is your responsibility to determine that this item is legal in your area. No returns on new items, and contact the manufacture for warranty info. Please ask all questions before purchasing.

title: For Sale:  FN SCAR 17S 7.62x51MM NATO/308 WIN. Black, w/11 Extra 20 Round Magazines
postcontent:
Brand New In The Box FN SCAR 17S all Black with one factory 20 round magazine, telescopic and folding stock, flip up sights and the owner’s manual. At last, the SCAR 17S is here. The new rifle is a semi-automatic-only version of the military’s selective-fire MK17 Mod 0 or Special Ops Combat Assault Rifle (SCAR) Heavy. Chambered in .308 Win./7.62x51 mm NATO, the gun is bigger and more powerful than its .223 Rem./5.56x45 mm NATO predecessor, the SCAR 16S, but, thankfully, not objectionably so. No longer constrained by limitations of that gun’s smaller receiver and chambering, the bigger SCAR 17S greatly expands the potential utility of the SCAR platform. One can argue that the SCAR Heavy was what Special Operations Command (SOCOM) wanted all along: a modern carbine chambered in 7.62x51 mm NATO that is lightweight, reliable and accurate.

Experience the long-range accuracy, downrange power, exceptional reliability and match winning versatility of the FN SCAR™ 17S, the semi-auto only version of the U.S. Special Operations Command’s newest service rifle. Chambered in 7.62x51mm NATO (308 Win.), the SCAR 17S features a free-floating, cold hammer-forged MIL-SPEC 16.25” barrel with hard chromed bore, 1 in 12” twist. Fully-ambidextrous operating controls instantly adapt the SCAR 17S to any user or any shooting position. The receiver-integrated MIL-STD 1913 optical rail plus three accessory rails enable mounting of a wide variety of scopes, electronic sights, tactical lights and lasers. The telescoping, side-folding polymer stock is fully adjustable for comb height and length of pull, making it ideal for Heavy Metal 3-Gun matches. O/A length is 28.5” folded, 38.5” extended. This gun weighs 8 pounds empty.

Also included in this sale is 11 extra magazines: 6 Flat Dark Earth and 5 Black.

I accept all major Credit Cards for a 2.75% fee. Check your local laws and make sure you can legally own this gun in your area. Local pick up is preferred! 
Buyer pays ALL transfer fees, but seller pays shipping.

title: For Trade:  Re: Magpul Pmag -- Let The Buyer Beware!
postcontent: Based on my own personal observations and recent contacts with several magazine sellers, I have found that a few bad-apple's on this website are misrepresenting their 1st generation Magpul Pmag's; as 2nd or 3rd generation, to try to rip more money from uninformed or unaware buyers.  A few even claim that their magazines are brand-new, when in fact they are actually used and some are even placed in non-factory common clear plastic and heat-sealed.  When questioned, one seller even said "Well.. a Pmag is a Pmag," which is @#$%^&!  If this was true, why would a company (such as Magpul) make improvements/modifications to their products thus creating 2nd, 3rd, 4th, generation models?  Don't fall for this shady @#$%^&! or overpay!  Before you hand over your hard-earned cash, do some simple research and know what the visual Pmag differences are and what the factory Magpul plastic packaging looks like.  Ads placed without photographs of the item are usually sketchy as well, so be cautious.  I hope this information helps some buyer out.  Good luck & God bless an armed America!
